1. Brute-force vhosts on the target system. What is the full subdomain that is prefixed with "web"? Answer using the full domain, e.g. "x.inlanefreight.htb"

All the following questions are the same except asking for different subdomains.

To use gobuster, you need to add <ip_address>  domainname to /etc/hosts, making sure to use a tab instead of single space between ip and domainname

this is so we can use -u http://inlanefreight.htb:port and the command knows which ip that should be.

you can skip the /etc/host step by using ffuf -u http://ip:port -H "Host:FUZZ.inlanefreight.htb -w wordlistpath.txt -ac
This is because the host is by -H and so we can use ip for -u instead of domainname for the host details. 
however, we need to use -ac in ffuf to do this to remove false positives. 
